  "diary": "Woke up to that perfect Sunday light filtering through my bedroom—the kind that made me grab my camera before even finishing my coffee. Walked over to Molly Moon's and just wandered Roosevelt with the lens, chasing shadows on brick and the way the morning sun caught storefront windows. Came home feeling restless in a good way, edited some shots while eating a brunch I'd been planning since yesterday's market trip.\n\nVolunteered at the food bank for an hour, which grounded me somehow. Then I drove out to Gas Works Park because the lake was calling—the water was alive with boats and kayakers, and I lost track of time photographing reflections and movement. There's something about watching other people play on the water that makes you feel less alone. Grabbed wine and groceries after, cooked a proper dinner at home, and ended the evening gaming with friends online while sorting through today's photos. Felt like a real day off.",
  "thought_process": "The weather was too good to waste indoors, so I leaned into the camera work early—it's my way of meditating, I guess. The volunteering wasn't planned as deeply as it sounds; it's just something I do most Sundays, keeps me connected to the community. But Lake Union was the real pull today. I think I needed to watch other people enjoying themselves, needed that reminder that life happens outside my kitchen. The cooking tonight felt less like work and more like play, probably because the whole day had that quality. My mood stayed even, almost buoyant—no stress, just presence.",
